# Python build / editable-install artifacts
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
build/
dist/
.pytest_cache/

# Derived, disposable data (invariant / decision 12): never read back by the engine
data/

# Timestamped backup archives (issue #38): the one artifact meant to outlive
# an accidental repo delete, deliberately not under data/ (which means "safe
# to delete"). No pruning; deleting an archive is a human act.
backups/

# Learner-produced solution artifacts for objective-gated nodes. The learner
# writes their solution here (the path each objective spec/checker points at) and
# submits it; the shipped seed carries no solutions, only the checkers that run
# against them. Keeping this untracked stops smoke-test and study artifacts from
# ever landing in the curriculum.
evidence/artifacts/*

# Carve-out (issue #28): prior-learning progress captures and cover sheets are
# committed evidence, not learner-produced solution scratch. Raw study notes
# never land here (kept privately outside the repo per the #27 amendment).
# (A directory-exclusion pattern here — `evidence/artifacts/` — can't be
# re-included by a negation below it; git won't descend into an excluded
# directory. `evidence/artifacts/*` excludes each entry individually instead,
# so the negation can un-ignore this one.)
!evidence/artifacts/prior_learning/
